children.subject: I don't have a lot of experience with these classes (I only took 47D - short version of 16A), but I'd encourage you to keep all the classes, graduate this semester and take a summer off (instead of taking one class) ;) I'm also enrolled in four tech classes plus blockchain DeCal, and I believe four tech are doable (although pretty hard).
I see. What's the link to the list of courses available this summer?

Are you trying to use these classes to fulfill degree requirements?

If that is the case, EE16A is the only class on your list that is offered this summer. So if you are trying to graduate and need all these classes and decide to drop one, EE16A is your only choice.

history.content: Imo 160 is the least useful course out of those, but I don't quite understand why you'll need to stay an extra semester if you drop one. Are you missing the requirements to graduate?

Hi everyone!

I'm taking these 4 technicals and nothing else. I'm concerned that they're too much. It's week two and I a bit stressed already. However, I don't care too much about a shiny GPA.

Has anyone taken these courses concurrently or had a similar schedule? Which one (between 160 and 161) should I drop if I decide to go that route?

This is my final semester as a CS student. If I drop a class, I'd stay an extra summer, which is fine by me. Should I bite the bullet this term or take a class this summer?

Thanks in advance!
